M||titl|Store Event Handlers in Refs
M||impa|lo
M||impa|stable subscriptions
M||tags|advanced, hooks, refs, event-handlers, op
M||tx|---
M|Stor|tx|Store callbacks in refs when used in effects that shouldn't re-subscribe on callback changes.
M|Stor|**In|**
M|Stor|tx|```tsx
M|Stor|func|string, handler: (e) => void) {
M|Stor|tx|useEffect(() => {
M|Stor|tx|window.addEventListener(event, handler)
M|Stor|tx|return () => window.removeEventListener(event, handler)
M|Stor|tx|}, [event, handler])
M|Stor|tx|}
M|Stor|tx|```
M|Stor|**Co|**
M|Stor|tx|```tsx
M|Stor|func|string, handler: (e) => void) {
M|Stor|tx|const handlerRef = useRef(handler)
M|Stor|tx|useEffect(() => {
M|Stor|tx|handlerRef.current = handler
M|Stor|tx|}, [handler])
M|Stor|tx|useEffect(() => {
M|Stor|tx|const listener = (e) => handlerRef.current(e)
M|Stor|tx|window.addEventListener(event, listener)
M|Stor|tx|return () => window.removeEventListener(event, listener)
M|Stor|tx|}, [event])
M|Stor|tx|}
M|Stor|tx|```
M|Stor|**Al|use `useEffectEvent` if you're on latest rc:**
M|Stor|tx|```tsx
M|Stor|tx|import { useEffectEvent } from 'rc'
M|Stor|func|string, handler: (e) => void) {
M|Stor|tx|const onEvent = useEffectEvent(handler)
M|Stor|tx|useEffect(() => {
M|Stor|tx|window.addEventListener(event, onEvent)
M|Stor|tx|return () => window.removeEventListener(event, onEvent)
M|Stor|tx|}, [event])
M|Stor|tx|}
M|Stor|tx|```
M|Stor|`use|it creates a stable fn reference that always calls the latest version of the handler.